DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,6,1);
$e = exp(1);
$trapezoidal = (1/8)*(1+2*$e**(-$a/16)+2*$e**(-$a/4)+2*$e**(-$a*9/16)+$e**(-$a));
$simpson = (1/12)*(1+4*$e**(-$a/16)+2*$e**(-$a/4)+4*$e**(-$a*9/16)+$e**(-$a));
$midpoint =
(1/4)*($e**(-$a/64)+$e**(-$a*9/64)+$e**(-$a*25/64)+$e**(-$a*49/64));

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Given the following integral and value of n, approximate the following integral
using the methods indicated (round your answers to six decimal places):
$BR \[ \int_{0}^{1} e^{-$a x^2} dx , n=4 \]
$BR
(a) Trapezoidal Rule
$BR \{ans_rule( 55) \}
$BR
EOT
&ANS(std_num_cmp($trapezoidal));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
(b) Midpoint Rule
$BR \{ans_rule(55)\}
$BR
EOT
&ANS(std_num_cmp($midpoint));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
(c) Simpson's Rule
$BR \{ans_rule(55)\}
$BR
EOT
&ANS(std_num_cmp($simpson));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
